text.__SUMMARY__:
Grevillea parviflora  is a shrub species in the family Proteaceae. It is native to the state of New South Wales  in Australia.  There are two subspecies:

G. parviflora subsp. parviflora,
G. parviflora subsp. supplicansIn the past, the name Grevillea parviflora was used for plants in Victoria which are now currently referred to the species  G. alpivaga,  G. gariwerdensis, G. micrantha, G.neurophylla or G. patulifolia.
